This is a classic Chicago dog restaurant. This is the place to go if you are a tourist looking for a properly grilled Chicago Dog, hint: burn the ends and dump relish in the cuts on the dog. Locals and construction workers hang out here, and grown ups who have memories of their favorite childhood train set. It’s a great place to take kids for pizza puffs and chili cheese fries. Oh! Also, this is a fun place to go post baseball games! They aren’t super crowded after Cubs games The food is super fresh and made to order. They take care of their customers so if you are allergic to anything let them know when you order. I highly recommend this restaurant !

This to me is Street Food, the Burgers, Maxwell Street style Polish, Fries, Fried Fish Sandwiches...but it also the décor, so it parallel the Lake Street El (elevated) train and get this, the outside seating has 4 original authentic train wheels, I kid you not! They are marked "Southern", and they huge. There are miniature train tracks circling to entire ceiling  of the interior and a battery operated train goes around this track continuously above your head while you eat, hence the name; Fast Track!

Best hotdog deal in town! The footlong char dog is a 12" long sausage wrapped in two 6" long poppyseed buns. Makes for an interesting eating scenario.The meal comes with all the fixings (watch out for the pickled jalapeño peppers), a generous side of fries (they say small), and a drink -- all for under $10. The staff bring out the Chicago flavor, and are the nicest bunch -- we got free lollipops at the end of the meal! Don't miss out!

My wife and I just had the best Italian dinner ever! Everything from the ambiance, to the lighting to the friendliness of the staff was just perfection. We both ordered total home runs of dishes, the Sorrentini gnnochi and the Fruitti Di Marre were SO good! It took us right back to the Amalfi coast. Plus, they brought us bruschetta, which we did not order as an app (complimentary) and a dessert (pana cotta) + port after our meal - all extras, on the house! The service was spectacular, and we will be back. Happy to have a new Italian spot!
